---
title: Box
description: Box is a general purpose low-level primitive with no specific semantics that can be used for layout and styling. All other layout primitives extend the Box primitive.
category: Layout
---

## Example

Use the `Box` layout primitive to access Keystar design tokens.

```jsx {% live=true %}
<Box
  backgroundColor="accent"
  border="accent"
  borderRadius="small"
  padding="large"
>
  <Text>Box example</Text>
</Box>
```

### Element type

By default, `Box` renders a div element. You can customise this using the
`elementType` prop. Non-style props will be forwarded to the underlying element.

```jsx
<Box elementType="section" id="element-type-example">
  ...
</Box>
```

## Props

The `Box` accepts all the [base style props](/package/style#reference), as well as the following:

### Border

| Name           | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 |
| -------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `border`       | Shorthand for the element's border on all four sides. It sets the values of border-width, border-style, and border-color. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border).                                               |
| `borderTop`    | Shorthand for the top border. It sets the values of border-width, border-style, and border-color. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-top).                                                                   |
| `borderBottom` | Shorthand for the bottom border. It sets the values of border-width, border-style, and border-color. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-bottom).                                                             |
| `borderStart`  | Shorthand for the border on the logical start side, depending on the layout direction. It sets the values of border-width, border-style, and border-color. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-inline-start). |
| `borderEnd`    | Shorthand for the border on the logical end side, depending on the layout direction. It sets the values of border-width, border-style, and border-color. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-inline-end).     |

### Border color

| Name               | Description                                                                                                                                                                  |
| ------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `borderColor`      | The color of the element's border on all four sides. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-color).                                               |
| `borderTopColor`   | The color of the top border. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-top-color).                                                                   |
| `borderBottomColor`| The color of the bottom border. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-bottom-color).                                                             |
| `borderStartColor` | The color of the border on the logical start side, depending on the layout direction. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-inline-start-color). |
| `borderEndColor`   | The color of the border on the logical end side, depending on the layout direction. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-inline-end-color).     |

