### Border radius

| Name                      | Description                                                                                                                                                                           |
| ------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `borderRadius`            | The border radius on all four sides of the element. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-radius).                                                        |
| `borderTopStartRadius`    | The border radius for the top start corner of the element, depending on the layout direction. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-start-start-radius).  |
| `borderTopEndRadius`      | The border radius for the top end corner of the element, depending on the layout direction. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-start-end-radius).      |
| `borderBottomStartRadius` | The border radius for the bottom start corner of the element, depending on the layout direction. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-end-start-radius). |
| `borderBottomEndRadius`   | The border radius for the bottom end corner of the element, depending on the layout direction. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-end-end-radius).     |


### Padding

| Name            | Description                                                                                                                                                    |
| --------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `padding`       | Sets the padding on all four sides of the element. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding).                                        |
| `paddingX`      | Sets the padding on the left and right sides of the element. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-inline-start).                 |
| `paddingY`      | Sets the padding on the top and bottom sides of the element. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-inline-end).                   |
| `paddingTop`    | Sets the padding on the top side of the element. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-top).                                      |
| `paddingBottom` | Sets the padding on the bottom side of the element. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-bottom).                                |
| `paddingStart`  | Sets the padding on the logical start side of the element, depending on layout direction. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding). |
| `paddingEnd`    | Sets the padding on the logical end side of the element, depending on layout direction. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding).   |

### Other

| Name            | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `backgroundColor`| The background color for the element. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/background-color).                                                                                                                        |
| `boxShadow`     | Adds shadow effects around an element's frame. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/box-shadow).                                                                                                                      |
| `cursor`        | The type of mouse cursor, if any, to show when the mouse pointer is over an element. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/cursor)                                                                                     |
| `opacity`       | The opacity of an element. Opacity is the degree to which content behind an element is hidden, and is the opposite of transparency. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/opacity)                                     |
| `overflow`      | Specify what to do when the element's content is too long to fit its size. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/overflow).                                                                                            |
| `pointerEvents` | Sets under what circumstances (if any) a particular element can become the target of pointer events. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/pointer-events).                                                            |
| `userSelect`    | Controls whether the user can select text. This doesn't have any effect on content loaded as part of a browser's user interface (its chrome), except in textboxes. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/user-select). |

